quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  39,53,"SAY: O my servants who have transgressed to your own hurt, despair not of God's mercy, for all sins doth God forgive. Gracious, Merciful is He"
  39,54,"And return ye to your Lord, and to Him resign yourselves, ere the punishment come on you, for then ye shall not be helped"
  39,55,"And follow that most excellent thing which hath been sent down to you from your Lord, ere the punishment come on you suddenly, and when ye look not for it"
  39,56,"So that a soul say, \"Oh misery! for my failures in duty towards God! and verily I was of those who scoffed"
  39,57,"Or say, \"Had God guided me, I had surely been of those who feared Him"
  39,58,"Or say, when it seeth the punishment, \"Could I but return, then I would be of the righteous"
  39,59,"Nay! my signs had already come to thee, and thou didst treat them as untruths, and wast arrogant, and becamest of those who believed not"
  39,60,"And on the resurrection day, thou shalt see those who have lied of God, with their faces black. Is there not an abode in Hell for the arrogant"
  39,61,"But God shall rescue those who fear him into their safe retreat: no ill shall touch them, neither shall they be put to grief"
  39,62,"God is the creator of all things, and of all things is He the guardian"
  39,63,His the keys of the Heavens and of the Earth! and - who believe not in the signs of God - these! they shall perish